author: Justin S
reviewBody: Seasons is definately one of the best dining halls at Iowa State. It is a relatively large hall, do there are usually tons of options when eating there. The buffet usually contains desirable dishes, but sometimes is just average. Definately check the ISU dining before going, to see if they have dishes you're interested in. Also, my opinion is that they have the best pizza of any other hall, which is a plus. They also have WORKING ice cream machines, and a whole ice cream topping center if you're into sweets. Also, it's nice to not thar Seasons is one of the two dining centers that are open throughout the whole weekend.Overall, seasons is one of the best dining halls, in my opinion.

reviewBody: Some of the food inherently sucks; Thats to be expected, kinda, at ISU. The best parts of Seasons are the greens, depending on the time and day, the sweets, and the Italian portion. The service is also inconsistent. Overall it's the weakest of the other dining locations on campus.

author: Logan Reel
reviewBody: Unless you plan on living off pizza and pasta during your time here at Iowa state seasons marketplace is absolutely terrible, everything is deep fried and sodium loaded , for example the wood grill has ribs with 3,210 mg of sodium per serving . (Youre meant to consume 2000mg max a day) the food is very unappetizing and the menus are very often misleading, often having things listed not available, and the only thing that would be somewhat macro nutrient friendly the bonsias has been closed for 3 weeks straight. If youre planning on eating after 7 30 pm forget it , unless like I mentioned you would like to live off burned pizza and stale pasta. Its ridiculous that students pay a mandatory $2,000 for a meal plan for which most days has next to nothing nutritious. As a first year student I dont plan on returning next year to live on campus, I hope they are able to make some changes and idk maybe have things that are actually beneficial to someones health rather than attempting to give people kidney stones with the insane amounts of sodium in the food options .
